<h3>Abstract</h3>

<p>

 This document attempts to define the goals and benefits of
 multihoming for fixed and mobile nodes (hosts and routers), i.e. from
 a node point of view, as investigated in the Monami6 WG, and not from
 a site point of view as investigated in the Shim6 WG. Those goals and
 benefits are illustrated with a set of scenarios. This document is
 generic in the sense that the benefits of node multihoming can be
 shared by both fixed end nodes and mobile end nodes. 
 It is intended to satisfy the first item as specified on the Monami6
 charter and as such, working group approval as a working group
 document will be sought.
 
</p><a name="toc"></a><br /><hr />
